# 00-compile
# project: uniqlogger

- clone the repository using a valid git <user>:
  > git clone https://<user>@gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/utils/uniqlogger.git
      i.e. git clone https://s.borghese@gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/utils/uniqlogger.git
- insert the password for the <user>

> cd uniqlogger/lib
- [optional] chechout the branch/tag to build:
  > git checkout tags/<version_no>
      i.e. git checkout tags/0.6.0
> cd lib
> export UNQLPATH=${PWD}
> cp depspath.pri.sample depspath.pri
- edit depspath.pri to suits your needs
> cp config.pri.sample config.pri

> cd src/ext
> git clone https://<user>@gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/utils/filecompressor.git filecompressor
> git clone https://<user>@gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/utils/dbhandler.git dbh
> git clone https://<user>@gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/utils/tpool tpool

> cd filecompressor
> cp config.pri.sample config.pri
> git clone https://gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/third-party/zlib.git third-party/zlib
> git clone https://gitlab.netresults.it:10443/netresults/third-party/minizip.git third-party/minizip
> cd third-party/zlib/lib
> ln -s <os>/ linux-64
- if you are building on Ubuntu 16.04 please check the ub1604-64b/README file 
> cd ${UNQLPATH}
> qmake-qt4 OR qmake-qt5
> make [debug|release]


